name: MSMessageErrorCode
desc: The error codes used in NSError objects generated by the Messages framework.

items.name: case fileNotFound
items.desc: The file could not be found.

items.name: case fileUnreadable
items.desc: The file could not be read.

items.name: case improperFileType
items.desc: The file is not a supported file type.

items.name: case improperFileURL
items.desc: The URL does not refer to a local file.

items.name: case stickerFileImproperFileAttributes
items.desc: The system cannot read one or more of the file’s attributes (for example, the file size).

items.name: case stickerFileImproperFileSize
items.desc: The image used to create an MSSticker object is larger than 500 KB.

items.name: case stickerFileImproperFileFormat
items.desc: The image used to create an MSSticker object is not one of the supported file types (PNG, APNG, GIF, or JPEG).

items.name: case urlExceedsMaxSize
items.desc: The URL in an MSMessage object’s url property is longer than the maximum allowed length (5,000 characters).

items.name: case sendWhileNotVisible
items.desc: A message was sent while the app was not visible.

items.name: case sendWithoutRecentInteraction
items.desc: A message was sent, but the app has not registered a recent touch interaction from the user.

items.name: case apiUnavailableInPresentationContext
items.desc: The API is unavailable in the current context.

items.name: case unknown
items.desc: An unexpected or unknown error has occurred.
